body: "## Charter\nLiving capability epic for storage, append-only history, and data durability: TOON item files, per-item history streams (hash-chained JSONL), checkpoints, gc, compaction, export/import, and format_version gating.\n\n## Scope\n- In: item-store write paths, history chain integrity (repair/redact/compact), gc scopes (locks/checkpoints/embeddings), backup/restore, format migrations.\n- Out: concurrency/locking semantics (pm-dj98 owns races and atomicity), search index storage (pm-ydp6).\n\n## Invariants this epic guards\n- History is append-only and hash-chained; appendLineAtomic is the only writer (see pm-y2ml docs).\n- Items must survive strict→lenient TOON decode fallback (2026-05-24 recovery precedent).\n- pm health history_drift must stay at 0 across 1400+ items.\n\n## Status\n20 closed children (compact snapshot, history-compact bulk + policy, gc scopes, restore hardening). Open as a living backlog — no open children at 2026-07-04; new durability work lands here."
